#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:2
msgid "export - compatibility function for exporting variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:7
msgid ""
"export\n"
"export NAME=VALUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:16
msgid ""
"``export`` is a function included for compatibility with POSIX shells. In "
"general, the :doc:`set <set>` builtin should be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:19
msgid ""
"When called without arguments, ``export`` prints a list of currently-"
"exported variables, like ``set -x``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:22
msgid ""
"When called with a ``NAME=VALUE`` pair, the variable ``NAME`` is set to "
"``VALUE`` in the global scope, and exported as an environment variable to "
"other commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:25
msgid "There are no options available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:28
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:30
msgid "The following commands have an identical effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:34
msgid ""
"set -gx PAGER bat\n"
"export PAGER=bat"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:37
msgid ""
"Note: If you want to add to e.g. ``$PATH``, you need to be careful to :ref:"
"`combine the list <cartesian-product>`. Quote it, like so::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:39
msgid "export PATH=\"$PATH:/opt/bin\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:41
msgid "Or just use ``set``, which avoids this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:43
msgid "set -gx PATH $PATH /opt/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:46
msgid "See more"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/export.rst:48
msgid "The :doc:`set <set>` command."
msgstr ""
